</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Let=E2=80=99s say that you think celeb=
rity stock-picker Cathie Wood is bad at picking stocks, and you want to bet=
 against her. Specifically you think that her flagship actively managed=C2=
=A0exchange-traded fund, the ARK Innovation ETF (ticker ARKK), will go down=
, and you would like to make money when it does. How would you do that? One=
 thing you could do is short all the stocks that she buys. You could do tha=
t reasonably effectively: ARK is an actively managed ETF, meaning that it c=
hanges its holdings unpredictably from time to time, but it <a href=3D"http=
