Professor Thaler, what do you make of current events in the stock markets? =
As a pioneer in the field of behavioral finance, these must be pretty excit=
ing times.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I sometimes play golf w=
ith my colleague Gene Fama, and if we were keeping score by what=E2=80=99s =
going on in the market rather than strokes made, I think I would be winning=
. Part of what seems to be going on I call the =E2=80=9Cbored market hypoth=
esis,=E2=80=9D because during the pandemic when people were working at home=
, especially in the beginning, they just had nothing to do. There weren=E2=
=80=99t even sports on television because all the games were cancelled. So =
there was nothing to bet on, and many people started individual investing.<=
/p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CAs a pioneer in the f=
ield of behavioral finance, these must be pretty exciting times=E2=80=9D is=
